{"comments":"RGB color molecule — composition of three Channel atoms.\n\nRGB (Red, Green, Blue) is the additive color model used by displays.\nEach channel represents light intensity from 0 (none) to 255 (full).\n\n- **Red**: Long wavelength light (~700nm)\n- **Green**: Medium wavelength light (~546nm)\n- **Blue**: Short wavelength light (~436nm)\n\n## Additive Color Mixing\n\n```\nRed + Green       = Yellow\nGreen + Blue      = Cyan\nBlue + Red        = Magenta\nRed + Green + Blue = White\n```\n\n## Device Dependency\n\nRGB values are device-dependent — the same values can appear differently\non different displays. For color-accurate work, use a color-managed\nworkflow with a defined color space (sRGB, Display P3, etc.).\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[100,32],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/RGB.purs","start":[100,1]},"title":"eqRGB"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[101,34],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/RGB.purs","start":[101,1]},"title":"ordRGB"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[104,24],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/RGB.purs","start":[103,1]},"title"